Last updated at 12:05AM, August 2 2013
Alcohol-related road deaths have risen for the first time in six years, official figures show, and experts say that last year’s big national events and cuts to the Government’s road safety advertising budget could be responsible. The number of people killed in drink-drive collisions last year rose by 25 per cent to 290, provisional data from the Department for Transport shows.
